      "Having both way sounds good to me. \r\n\r\n```\r\nobj = { }\r\nobj(\"counts\")(\"key\", 0) => error\r\nobj(\"counts\")(\"key\").default(0) => 0\r\n\r\n-----------------\r\n\r\nobj = { count: { } }\r\nobj(\"counts\")(\"key\", 0) => 0\r\nobj(\"counts\")(\"key\").default(0) => 0\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\nSo `.defaults` would be a `try/catch` and supplying the default value in the function would be like using the existential operator.\r\nI would rename default() to `catch` if we get both solutions too."
